# Racial Capitalism - Savage to Slave Link  

**Summary**: The "savage to slave" trope, as explored in `[[Africana Studies - Savage-to-Slave]]`, exemplifies racial capitalism—European powers dehumanized Africans to extract labor, per Cedric Robinson’s *Black Marxism*. This narrative erased African agency (e.g., Kongo, Mali) to justify exploitation, fueling global inequities.  

**Details**: Europe’s labor demand post-**Great Dying** drove mass enslavement, masking theft as "inevitable progress." This aligns with Walter Rodney’s *How Europe Underdeveloped Africa*, showing how racial hierarchies propped up economic systems—still echoes in modern carceral logic (Michelle Alexander’s *The New Jim Crow*).  

